primary_outcome.description:
The primary endpoint of interest is PFS12 defined as the proportion of patients without progressive disease per RECIST 1.1 at 12 weeks after treatment initiation. A sample size of 10 evaluable patients per disease cohort (soft tissue and bone) will allow for the estimation of PFS12 per the 90% exact confidence intervals as follows:
PFS12 Exact 90% confidence interval:
1/10 10% (1-39%); 2/10 20% (4-51%); 3/10 30% (9-61%); 4/10 40% (15-70%); 5/10 50% (22-78%); 6/10 60% (30-85%); 7/10 70% (39-91%); 8/10 80% (49-96%); 9/10 90% (61-99%);
